33 /********************************************************************
34 *
35 * Standard register and bit definitions for the Texas Instruments
36 * MSP430 microcontroller.
37 *
38 * This file supports assembler and C development for
39 * MSP430FR5XX_FR6XXGENERIC device.
40 *
41 * Texas Instruments, Version 1.0
42 *
43 * Rev. 1.0, Setup
44 *
45 *
46 ********************************************************************/

59 /* PERIPHERAL FILE MAP */

61 
62 #ifndef SFR_8BIT
63 /* External references resolved by a device-specific linker command file */
64 #define SFR_8BIT(address) extern volatile unsigned char address
65 #define SFR_16BIT(address) extern volatile unsigned int address
66 //#define SFR_20BIT(address) extern volatile unsigned int address
67 typedef void (* __SFR_FARPTR)();
68 #define SFR_20BIT(address) extern __SFR_FARPTR address
69 #define SFR_32BIT(address) extern volatile unsigned long address
70 
71 #endif
72

74 /************************************************************
75 * STANDARD BITS
76 ************************************************************/
77 
78 #define BIT0 (0x0001)
79 #define BIT1 (0x0002)
80 #define BIT2 (0x0004)
81 #define BIT3 (0x0008)
82 #define BIT4 (0x0010)
83 #define BIT5 (0x0020)
84 #define BIT6 (0x0040)
85 #define BIT7 (0x0080)
86 #define BIT8 (0x0100)
87 #define BIT9 (0x0200)
88 #define BITA (0x0400)
89 #define BITB (0x0800)
90 #define BITC (0x1000)
91 #define BITD (0x2000)
92 #define BITE (0x4000)
93 #define BITF (0x8000)
94 
95 /************************************************************
96 * STATUS REGISTER BITS
97 ************************************************************/
98 
99 #define C (0x0001)
100 #define Z (0x0002)
101 #define N (0x0004)
102 #define V (0x0100)
103 #define GIE (0x0008)
104 #define CPUOFF (0x0010)
105 #define OSCOFF (0x0020)
106 #define SCG0 (0x0040)
107 #define SCG1 (0x0080)
108 
109 /* Low Power Modes coded with Bits 4-7 in SR */
110 
111 #ifdef __ASM_HEADER__ /* Begin #defines for assembler */
112 #define LPM0 (CPUOFF)
113 #define LPM1 (SCG0+CPUOFF)
114 #define LPM2 (SCG1+CPUOFF)
115 #define LPM3 (SCG1+SCG0+CPUOFF)
116 #define LPM4 (SCG1+SCG0+OSCOFF+CPUOFF)
117 /* End #defines for assembler */
118 
119 #else /* Begin #defines for C */
120 #define LPM0_bits (CPUOFF)
121 #define LPM1_bits (SCG0+CPUOFF)
122 #define LPM2_bits (SCG1+CPUOFF)
123 #define LPM3_bits (SCG1+SCG0+CPUOFF)
124 #define LPM4_bits (SCG1+SCG0+OSCOFF+CPUOFF)
125 
126 #include "in430.h"
127 #include <intrinsics.h>
128 
129 #if __MSP430_HEADER_VERSION__ < 1107
130  #define LPM0 _bis_SR_register(LPM0_bits) /* Enter Low Power Mode 0 */
131  #define LPM0_EXIT _bic_SR_register_on_exit(LPM0_bits) /* Exit Low Power Mode 0 */
132  #define LPM1 _bis_SR_register(LPM1_bits) /* Enter Low Power Mode 1 */
133  #define LPM1_EXIT _bic_SR_register_on_exit(LPM1_bits) /* Exit Low Power Mode 1 */
134  #define LPM2 _bis_SR_register(LPM2_bits) /* Enter Low Power Mode 2 */
135  #define LPM2_EXIT _bic_SR_register_on_exit(LPM2_bits) /* Exit Low Power Mode 2 */
136  #define LPM3 _bis_SR_register(LPM3_bits) /* Enter Low Power Mode 3 */
137  #define LPM3_EXIT _bic_SR_register_on_exit(LPM3_bits) /* Exit Low Power Mode 3 */
138  #define LPM4 _bis_SR_register(LPM4_bits) /* Enter Low Power Mode 4 */
139  #define LPM4_EXIT _bic_SR_register_on_exit(LPM4_bits) /* Exit Low Power Mode 4 */
140 #else
141  #define LPM0 __bis_SR_register(LPM0_bits) /* Enter Low Power Mode 0 */
142  #define LPM0_EXIT __bic_SR_register_on_exit(LPM0_bits) /* Exit Low Power Mode 0 */
143  #define LPM1 __bis_SR_register(LPM1_bits) /* Enter Low Power Mode 1 */
144  #define LPM1_EXIT __bic_SR_register_on_exit(LPM1_bits) /* Exit Low Power Mode 1 */
145  #define LPM2 __bis_SR_register(LPM2_bits) /* Enter Low Power Mode 2 */
146  #define LPM2_EXIT __bic_SR_register_on_exit(LPM2_bits) /* Exit Low Power Mode 2 */
147  #define LPM3 __bis_SR_register(LPM3_bits) /* Enter Low Power Mode 3 */
148  #define LPM3_EXIT __bic_SR_register_on_exit(LPM3_bits) /* Exit Low Power Mode 3 */
149  #define LPM4 __bis_SR_register(LPM4_bits) /* Enter Low Power Mode 4 */
150  #define LPM4_EXIT __bic_SR_register_on_exit(LPM4_bits) /* Exit Low Power Mode 4 */
151 #endif
152 #endif /* End #defines for C */

5690 #define CCIS_3 (3*0x1000u)

5693 #define CM_2 (2*0x4000u) /* Capture mode: 1 - neg. edge */
5694 #define CM_3 (3*0x4000u) /* Capture mode: 1 - both edges */

5704 #define SCCI (0x0400) /* Latched capture signal (read) */

5706 #define CCI (0x0008) /* Capture input signal (read) */

5708 #define ID__2 (1*0x40u) /* Timer B input divider: 1 - /2 */

5712 #define ID_1 (1*0x40u) /* Timer B input divider: 1 - /2 */

6437 /* WDT-interval times [1ms] coded with Bits 0-2 */
6438 /* WDT is clocked by fSMCLK (assumed 1MHz) */
6439 #define WDT_MDLY_32 (WDTPW+WDTTMSEL+WDTCNTCL+WDTIS2) /* 32ms interval (default) */
6440 #define WDT_MDLY_8 (WDTPW+WDTTMSEL+WDTCNTCL+WDTIS2+WDTIS0) /* 8ms " */
6441 #define WDT_MDLY_0_5 (WDTPW+WDTTMSEL+WDTCNTCL+WDTIS2+WDTIS1) /* 0.5ms " */
6442 #define WDT_MDLY_0_064 (WDTPW+WDTTMSEL+WDTCNTCL+WDTIS2+WDTIS1+WDTIS0) /* 0.064ms " */
6443 /* WDT is clocked by fACLK (assumed 32KHz) */
6444 #define WDT_ADLY_1000 (WDTPW+WDTTMSEL+WDTCNTCL+WDTIS2+WDTSSEL0) /* 1000ms " */
6445 #define WDT_ADLY_250 (WDTPW+WDTTMSEL+WDTCNTCL+WDTIS2+WDTSSEL0+WDTIS0) /* 250ms " */
6446 #define WDT_ADLY_16 (WDTPW+WDTTMSEL+WDTCNTCL+WDTIS2+WDTSSEL0+WDTIS1) /* 16ms " */
6447 #define WDT_ADLY_1_9 (WDTPW+WDTTMSEL+WDTCNTCL+WDTIS2+WDTSSEL0+WDTIS1+WDTIS0) /* 1.9ms " */
6448 /* Watchdog mode -> reset after expired time */
6449 /* WDT is clocked by fSMCLK (assumed 1MHz) */
6450 #define WDT_MRST_32 (WDTPW+WDTCNTCL+WDTIS2) /* 32ms interval (default) */
6451 #define WDT_MRST_8 (WDTPW+WDTCNTCL+WDTIS2+WDTIS0) /* 8ms " */
6452 #define WDT_MRST_0_5 (WDTPW+WDTCNTCL+WDTIS2+WDTIS1) /* 0.5ms " */
6453 #define WDT_MRST_0_064 (WDTPW+WDTCNTCL+WDTIS2+WDTIS1+WDTIS0) /* 0.064ms " */
6454 /* WDT is clocked by fACLK (assumed 32KHz) */
6455 #define WDT_ARST_1000 (WDTPW+WDTCNTCL+WDTSSEL0+WDTIS2) /* 1000ms " */
6456 #define WDT_ARST_250 (WDTPW+WDTCNTCL+WDTSSEL0+WDTIS2+WDTIS0) /* 250ms " */
6457 #define WDT_ARST_16 (WDTPW+WDTCNTCL+WDTSSEL0+WDTIS2+WDTIS1) /* 16ms " */
6458 #define WDT_ARST_1_9 (WDTPW+WDTCNTCL+WDTSSEL0+WDTIS2+WDTIS1+WDTIS0) /* 1.9ms " */

6487 /************************************************************
6488 * Interrupt Vectors (offset from 0xFF80)
6489 ************************************************************/
6490 
6491 #pragma diag_suppress 1107
6492 #define VECTOR_NAME(name) name##_ptr
6493 #define EMIT_PRAGMA(x) _Pragma(#x)
6494 #define CREATE_VECTOR(name) void * const VECTOR_NAME(name) = (void *)(long)&name
6495 #define PLACE_VECTOR(vector,section) EMIT_PRAGMA(DATA_SECTION(vector,section))
6496 #define PLACE_INTERRUPT(func) EMIT_PRAGMA(CODE_SECTION(func,".text:_isr"))
6497 #define ISR_VECTOR(func,offset) CREATE_VECTOR(func); \
6498  PLACE_VECTOR(VECTOR_NAME(func), offset) \
6499  PLACE_INTERRUPT(func)
